      <bioghist id="aspace_03b4e4eda5e40124d8c83bf6f0ae3a23">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>John Reynolds (1791 December to 1868 September) was a school teacher based out of London. Volume 3 of <title>
               <part>Modern English biography[...]</part>
            </title> by Frederic Boase notes that he was part of the founding of the London Mechanists Institute (now Birkbeck, University of London) where he taught French and geography, and the London Gymnasium.   He ran a school out of 23 Chadwell Street, Pentonvile from 1842 to his death, and authored several school books such as <title>
               <part>The Young Ladies Guide to Arithmetic</part>
            </title> (1858) and <title>
               <part>Definitions of the Various Terms and Figures in Geometery</part>
            </title> (1850).</p>
         <p>John Reynolds is buried in Highgate Cemetary, London.</p>
      </bioghist>
